Gauteng Education spokesperson Steve Mabona says the boys were both from Freedom Park Secondary and police are investigating the incident. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - In yet another incident of school violence in Gauteng, a 14-year-old boy has been stabbed to death allegedly by another pupil. Gauteng Education spokesperson, Steve Mabona, says the boys were both from Freedom Park Secondary and police are investigating the incident. The spokesperson said the stabbing allegedly was an escalation of a fight between the two boys. Mabona says he has no information on whether the suspect has been arrested. The stabbing happened after school near their homes.